The paper deals with graph problems and their streaming complexity, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and algorithms (cs.AL). The focus on parameterized streaming complexity narrows down the possible sub-categories, and the specific problems and models studied in the paper suggest that cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT, and cs.AL are the most likely sub-categories.
